<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Python on Mapping Black Philly Art</title><link>https://artvizphilly.github.io/tags/python/</link><description>Recent content in Python on Mapping Black Philly Art</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 22 Aug 2022 11:13:32 -0400</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://artvizphilly.github.io/tags/python/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Visualizing Wikidata with Python</title><link>https://artvizphilly.github.io/post/python/</link><pubDate>Mon, 22 Aug 2022 11:13:32 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://artvizphilly.github.io/post/python/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;For this project, we used Python to run SPARQL queries against Wikidata and turn the results into interactive visualizations. The main tools are &lt;a href="https://sparqlwrapper.readthedocs.io/"&gt;SPARQLWrapper&lt;/a&gt; for querying and &lt;a href="https://plotly.com/python/"&gt;Plotly&lt;/a&gt; for visualization.&lt;/p&gt;
